page.title: 01Landscape
page.content: The area is situated south of the A.55 and it is also south of the village of St.George and south west of the village of Bodelwyddan. The area has no village within its boundary. It is mainly agricultural land and although there is a park land marked on the map, this land is also used for farming. There is the river Elwy that flows from west to east at the southern extremity of the area. The area is of lowland but has several hills, but these do not rise to any significant height and the overall impression is that of undulation. To view the area as a whole it would be necessary to climb to the top of MOELFRE ISAF 1086'which is outside the perimeter of the given area in a westerly direction.
